          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Expanding Access to Prescription Drug Monitoring Programs Act</b></p> This bill amends the Public Health Service Act and revises the Harold Rogers Prescription Drug Monitoring Program to require a state receiving grant funds for a prescription drug monitoring program to make relevant prescription information available to all individuals authorized by the state to prescribe controlled substances, including nurse practitioners and physician assistants.]]></text>
          <updateDate>2016-02-02T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
